unclear /ʌnˈklɪə/

ADJ If something is unclear , it is not known or not certain. 未知的; 不确定的 

例： It is unclear how much popular support they have among the island's population. 不知道他们在该岛居民中有多少民众支持。 

例： Just what the soldier was doing there is unclear. 那个士兵在那儿到底在干什么不得而知。 

2. ADJ If you are unclear about something, you do not understand it well or are not sure about it. 不明白的; 不清楚的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： He is still unclear about his own future. 他对自己的未来仍不清楚。

